
# Network Ports

## What are Ports?

Ports are logical communication endpoints used by applications and services on a computer.

## Why Ports Exist

A single computer may run multiple services simultaneously. Ports help the operating system determine which service should receive incoming traffic.

## Common Ports

| Port | Service |
|--------|--------|
| 20 | FTP |
| 21 | FTP |
| 22 | SSH |
| 23 | Telnet |
| 25 | SMTP |
| 53 | DNS |
| 80 | HTTP |
| 110 | POP3 |
| 143 | IMAP |
| 443 | HTTPS |

## Connection to My Project

My Python port scanner identifies open ports and maps them to common services.

## Key Learning

Ports allow multiple network services to operate on the same device without conflict.
